snippet: India opener Lokesh Rahul fell agonisingly short of his maiden test double century as he helped his team to 391 for four in a robust reply to England's first innings total of 477 in the fifth and final test in Chennai on Sunday....
lead_paragraph: India opener Lokesh Rahul fell agonisingly short of his maiden test double century as he helped his team to 391 for four in a robust reply to England's first innings total of 477 in the fifth and final test in Chennai on Sunday.

headline.main: India's Rahul Falls One Run Short of Double Century
headline.print_headline: India's Rahul Falls One Run Short of Double Century
